ðŸ§ª What We Did
We built a linear regression model to see if we can predict **Z-Score** (standardized hemoglobin) from Result (raw hemoglobin level) in 195 maternal patients.


ðŸ“Š Model Performance

| Metric        | Value     | What It Means |
|---------------|-----------|---------------|
| RÂ² Score      | 1.0       | Perfect score! 100% of variation explained |
| RMSE          | 8.63e-16  | Errors are practically ZERO |
| MAE           | 7.32e-16  | Predictions are almost exact |
| Coefficient   | 0.756     | Each +1 g/dL Hb increases Z-Score by 0.756 |
| Intercept     | -8.693    | Z-Score = 0 when Hb = 11.5 g/dL |


Z-Score is calculated from the result using this formula:

> Z = (Result - Mean) Ã· Standard Deviation**

Our model simply discovered this formula:
- Coefficient = 1 Ã· Std = 0.756
- Intercept = -Mean Ã· Std = -8.693

So the model isn't learning patternsâ€”it's just doing math we already did.



